Journal Story: First day, up to springer mountain
Day two, met up with Don from Virginia ,tent camp beside stream,also met Marie,and Mike.received some trail magic, water and Gatorade from ribeye
Not quite a mile today, decided to stay here and rest for the day.Mike from Virginia caught up with me.

Good day of hiking, made it to, met Catlin and Erica I call them the cruising girls for now until they get trail name's. Also met Texas George, received trail magic at Woody gap hot dogs, brownies, and water, ( tic tock ).

made it to Neel gap, dropped the two man tent 5.8 lbs., bought a new tent 2.8oz needed to drop some weight, it was tough climbing with my heavy pack. I was able to get my pack weight down to 38lbs.recieved some chick flay burgers and some soda's [trail magic), food and drinks donated by past AT thru hikers, what a blessing. met Jordan from Texas, Spaghetti legs-cotton-just to name a few of the thru hikers that I have met.

pictures will not always be from the same day, hiked 1.2 miles off trail to shelter, met up with Bees-Bones-Crooked foot and silent Bob, sleep in my new tent, very nice.Starting to get toes jammed into boots, so many gaps and summits some times 200ft to 1000ft up and downs, it crazy.
not much just hiking, enjoying the hiker fellowship, most of my current tribe are in their mid 20's just parting and having fun.
spent the night at The Top Of Georgia hostel, was able to get a shower ( well needed) and comfort. I have some video clips, I just need to figure out how to get them loaded.

Stayed at The Top of the mountain Georgia, also with Puma,flipper, eric,bees, and bones / had to buy a new stove / met Sir packs a lotnow completed 52.9 miles of the trail only averaged 7.3 miles a day this week and a long way to go.
Cold night in the shelter, 22degrees, hikers thinning out. Met up with Vinny , hatchet,shadow, Crooked Foot, and Silent Bob.
Just another day on the trail.
Lots of NoBo's here
Saturday .Reached camp at 4pm set up Tent, then it started to rain, only one day of food left, will have to go into town ( Franklin NC tomorrow).

106.0 hiking today with crooked foot and shadow, met for the first time dana,putts,and Katie. tent pad was on a slight angle the first of many nights that I would roll down in the sleeping bag inside the tent, obviously not to far. Also met burnsaw and lost dog.

Not much of a hike down to the gap from the shelter to get picked up by Ron Harper and Baltimore Jack who shuttled all of us into Franklin to the budget inn, owned and operated by Ron ( former 1970's wrestler ) Shared a cottage room with crooked foot and shadow, magic pizza night. resupplied , enjoyed pancake breakfast at the church, great service provided with a picture and post card. Gave my tablet and beats head phones to shadow along with my heavier charging pack to reduce my pack weight. No more movies at night in my tent, it was hard to let go of and at the same time good.

The start of week #3 Easter sunday, had a great breakfast at the church in Franklin this morning, hiked onto the trail with Katie today later to be given the trail name of Pluto, at the start of trail Tic put some trail magic eggs with chocolate in the along side the trail. Trail magic also left in a cooler , enjoyed a V-8 and banana. Crooked foot, shadow and many other hikers at the shelter tonight, kickit and larrybird also.
Someday I will get all the pictures to line up with these entries.
Toes are getting pretty sore from all the long steep down hill gaps.
Tented on a ridge with Vinny ( later to become one shot , mainly because of his ability to get his bear bag cord hung in one shot with his sling shot method. also met blacksmith and Jimmy cricket.
Tuesday, tough down hill trail today, tented, beautiful tower views today on gopro video have to get uploaded later. will hike into the NOC tommorow

NOC center stopped in here today, outfitters to print out my Smokies permit only 1 mile from the shelter then 6.7 out to Sassafras.
Met up with bees and bones again, along with shotgun carried a bag of wine up to the shelter (likes to party, former air line stewart ), happyfeet(german)
tumbleweed formerly with pluto now hiking with shotgun. Lots of trial buddy changing going on, this trend will continue.
Was heading to Cabin in the Woods, picked up by Philip, and met Donna at the cabins.cool place with great services.Stayed two nights then slack packed out to FOntana Dam.
Stayed again
Sack packed with ETA to Fontana villiage then hiked into the fontana hilton amongst many other hikers. Left big toe nail not doing so well and i will probably lose it.
Day 32 staying at the Sunny bank inn great old house hostel owned and run by Elmer.
short day into hostel 1 mile out from erwin, Tennesee
Destination: devils fork gap to Uncle Jonny's

Journal Story: Short hike into the Mountain Harbour BB/Hostel for a good nights rest for my birthday tomorrow. They had a great breakfast.
Short hike into the Mountain Harbour BB/Hostel for a good nights rest for my birthday tomorrow. They had a great breakfast.

made the challenge from the Vandeventer Shelter down into Damascus Va.Left the shelter at 5am and arrived in town at 8;15 just before the down pour and storm hit,stayed at the place the first night then stayed at the Woodchuck hostel in a teepee on my zero day.
Start location: devils fork gap to Uncle Jonny's

Journal Story: Slack pack from hostel.
Hiked with Chef Tumbleweed and Joker/, and tented with Savior / scooter-formerly roadrunner.826.7 miles completed.

Hiked into reeds gap with Cheddar and hitched a ride into Devils Backbone brewing company, they let hikers camp for free, great place , great food, and they tell me that the micro beers here were great too. Enjoyed the fellowship with they other hikers about 30 of us stayed here for the night, they also made us 5 a 5 dollar breakfast, it was outstanding. Will post some pic's later.

Made it into town today for re-supply and shower, showered at the YMC and will be staying at the Grace Lutheran church hostel tonight with free dinner.I am now at mile 861 of the trail, and feeling good about everything.

Headed out of town, enjoyed a great stay at the church, met up with T3,Shiv, and Nature for start of a new pak of hikers " THE NAT PAK "Saw a section hiker group also heading out with a toilet seat.Ended up putting up my tarp before my tent because of the rain.

Hiked into town with T3 and Shivtotal miles at this time into the ATC head quarters was 1023.1 what we call the mental halfway point for the northbound hikers going to maine. Feels great to of reach this place, found a brand new pair of hiking boots in the hiker box, they said someone left them because of the blisters they started to get with them and that they were not able to return them, what a blessing , and to think that they were the right size for me. My salmons were really getting wore down, i was not sure they would of made it the rest of the way , and i did not have the money for new ones, but the lord does provide.
Long day push to campsite with Nat Pak and Snickers and Elsa
Destination: Camp, past Pine Grove Furnace/1105.3 mile

Journal Story: Outstanding trail angel magic fromm Bobby Goodyear, picked all us up on our way to the store to re-supply, Ummgahwah / Nature /T3, Shiv / and Joker
Hiked about 15.6 miles with the Nat Pak ,snickers and elsa, joker ,and dreamer, then we freedom hike because of the trail Angel Mary into town and stayed at her place.

Stayed a second night at Mary's Joker and Snickers and Elsa and Dreamer hiked on. This was a nice little town, but old with the Doyle bar and resturante if you want to call it that. They rooms for rent , but we still stayed at Mary's, heard too many bad things about the rooms at the Doyle.

One more night, Nat pak broke up today as planned, Nature had to go to a wedding for a friend to return to the trail on Monday, and Shiv and T3 are working on their way to Germany and plan to return to the trail in 4 weeks and my catch up to me.Shiv and T3 were married back in February and then started vthe trail as part of their honeymoon.

Left the Wiley Shelter this morning to hike into Kent Ct for a re-supply with Nature, it was a pleasant day of hiking. Picked up a ride from the parking lot just as we were leaving the trail.I have a lot of catching up to do with my journals, but this is not the time.1454.0 to 1466.7 miles hiked through 9 states in # 10 right now.
Silverstreak - It was great seeing you again! Have a safe trip home
Hiking down Moosilaka mountain 4800+ . spent the night in the Boone shelter with Nature and some SOBO's after a steep climb up with lots of rocks, beautiful views. Staying at hotel in Woodstock, N.H
